&lt;Carter-Day Industries Inc>said its Hart-Carter Co subsidizary has sold substantially allof its assets used in the production and sale of farmmachinery for 500,000 dlrs below book value in cash and notes.    It said substantially all of the proceeds from thetransaction are committed to application against advances fromsecured lenders, accounts payable and accrued liabilities.    The company said for the nine months ended December 31, theoperations being sold had revenues of 8,105,000 dlrs and lost146,000 dlrs. Reuter&#3;